                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d819">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.6211/411a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="2" xml:id="d819fn2">The same, on the same date, with
                        reference to Department’s 2000, to the Ambassador in France (No.
                        2003).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-07T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4410. Department’s 4396, 5 p.m. Inasmuch as Department is anxious that <hi
                        rend="italic">Frederik VIII</hi> should sail on February 13, it is important
                    that assurances of safe-conduct be obtained immediately The Scandinavian Line,
                    in addition, desires assurances that no objection will be raised to the <hi
                        rend="italic">Frederik VIII</hi> carrying other passengers, mails, and
                    cargo, as usual.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
